installing a ridge vent inmy attic i have gable vents and i want to take them out and put in gable windows in order to keep the attic ventalated i want to install a ridge vent i have a chimney going up thru the center of my attic and thru the ridge of my roof can i still install a ridge vent there you should be able to install ridge vents on the roof on each side of the chimney while you are working on this you should double check that your soffit vents are clear of insulation if you don't have soffit vents then you should add them too and install baffles between the roof rafters to keep attic insulation from getting pushed over the soffit vents and against the underside of your roof sheathing and blocking the air flow from the soffit vents Tilia Woodworking Rail transport modelling Humidor Humidifier Wood Piano Humidity Urinary incontinence Amalienborg Palace Wood carving Houseplant Dehumidifier Torquay United F.C. Poker jargon Oakland Athletics Ernest Harmon Air Force Base Scale model Crucible Top-bar hive Chisel Cello History of ancient Egypt Hemp Upholstery Harmonic oscillator 2005 Atlantic hurricane season Bali Thunderstorm Battles of Lexington and Concord International League Laws of cricket Polyethylene terephthalate Appalachian Mountains Tenshinhan Michael Garibaldi GunZ The Duel Civil engineering and infrastructure repair in New Orleans after Hurricane Katrina Guitar Ferengi DeviantART George Lohmann Bronchoconstriction Gypsy moth Osella Topps Desert Ford Mustang Riparian strips U.S. 82nd Airborne Division Coventry City F.C. Hay Disneyland Leeds United F.C. Glossary of wildland fire terms Weather forecasting Overclocking Sand casting The Tenth Planet Fifth Beatle Pachypodium Moisturizer Comet Baking Royal Brunei Humphrey Bogart Nose Nasal congestion Ankh-Morpork City Watch Bedwetting NeXT AMC V8 engine 2003 United States Grand Prix Air conditioning Precipitation (meteorology) Radeon Laguna province De Lorean DMC-12 Chan Wah-shun History of the Beatles Wild 